The '''silver-crowned friarbird''' ('''''Philemon argenticeps''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Meliphagidae]].It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to northern [[Australia]], including [[Queensland]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Species profile—Philemon argenticeps (silver-crowned friarbird) |url=https://apps.des.qld.gov.au/species-search/details/?id=1491 |access-date=2024-04-04 |website=Species information |publisher=Queensland Government}}</ref>

Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical dry [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical mangrove forests.

